  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nOur nodes are currently running nethermind 1.12.4 but the nethermind apt package for the new release is not available. See output of `apt-cache policy nethermind`:\r\n```\r\nnethermind:\r\n  Installed: 1.1240\r\n  Candidate: 1.1240\r\n  Version table:\r\n *** 1.1240 500\r\n        500 http://ppa.launchpad.net/nethermindeth/nethermind/ubuntu bionic/main amd64 Packages\r\n        100 /var/lib/dpkg/status\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I uninstall the package and re-install, I do end up with the latest nethermind release (`1.12.7`) but the apt package is still version `1.1240`. My feeling is that the PPA repo is not correctly updated, I should be able to see and install a `1.1270` version of the apt package.\r\n\r\nThis is affecting our upgrade process as ansible thinks there is no later release to install.",
