    "body": "Hello @ayazabbas. I tried to replicate your issue in a fresh Ubuntu 20.04 LTS VPS. This is what I did using a user with root access:\r\n```\r\n 1  add-apt-repository ppa:nethermindeth/nethermind\r\n 2  apt-get update\r\n 3  apt-cache policy nethermind\r\n 4  apt install nethermind\r\n 5  apt-cache policy nethermind\r\n```\r\n\r\nFirst `apt-cache policy nethermind` output:\r\n```\r\nnethermind:\r\n  Installed: (none)\r\n  Candidate: 1.1270\r\n  Version table:\r\n     1.1270 500\r\n        500 http://ppa.launchpad.net/nethermindeth/nethermind/ubuntu focal/main amd64 Packages\r\n```\r\n\r\nSecond:\r\n```\r\nnethermind:\r\n  Installed: 1.1270\r\n  Candidate: 1.1270\r\n  Version table:\r\n *** 1.1270 500\r\n        500 http://ppa.launchpad.net/nethermindeth/nethermind/ubuntu focal/main amd64 Packages\r\n        100 /var/lib/dpkg/status\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe updated the PPA repository with the release 1.1270 two days ago and on https://launchpad.net/~nethermindeth/+archive/ubuntu/nethermind is everything ok . By any chance your `apt update`  is not working properly or your cache is corrupted?",
